DTEND:20260611T151500Z
SUMMARY:YĪN YĪN
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Energetic genre-scrambling groove-machine\n\nDutch collective Y
 ĪN YĪN scramble global movements in a blender: psych rock\, Thai funk\
 , Japanese city pop... anything that tickles their current fancy.\nTheir o
 mnivorous spirit often unfolds in some of the most succulent grooves imagi
 nable\, with a vibrant assembly of traditional instruments\, vintage synth
 s and flavorful percussion spicing everything up. YĪN YĪN have truly p
 erfected the art of musical fusion cooking.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a6f03b681e402b55@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T161500Z
DTEND:20260611T171500Z
SUMMARY:Curtis Harding
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Modern soul man with deep bag\n\nWith a cool you simply can’t
  teach\, Curtis Harding instills his honed psychedelic sound with pure sou
 l\, gospel\, garage and funk.Harding has made a habit out of stepping into
  new musical situations like a wide-eyed student – only to seemlessly ab
 sorb them as if they're always part of his DNA. A true chameleon who keeps
  on shining in whatever musical context he operates – his sights perpetu
 ally set on the next time he shuffles his now extensive deck of influences
 .
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d141ab6f61a9ce52@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T181500Z
DTEND:20260611T191500Z
SUMMARY:De La Soul
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:High rising hip-hop legends\n\nSince their landmark LP 3 High a
 nd Rising\, De La Soul has been a revolutionary force in hip-hop and music
  in general.\nThey opened the floodgates of what rap could be\, sampling e
 lements of pop\, jazz\, reggae and psychedelia\, plus using fun and flippa
 ncy as a counterbalance. The dawn of Da Inner Sound throughout the decades
  wasn’t without its tragedies\, as founding member Trugoy The Dove passe
 d away in 2023. The remaining members ran it back with 2025’s beaming Ca
 bin In The Sky: no rest for the wicked livin’ in the fulltime era.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-6b45231696dd5a69@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T203000Z
DTEND:20260611T220000Z
SUMMARY:Jack White
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Rock music's chief anti-hero\n\nA legendary guitar hero in days
  where that concept seems rarer and rarer\, Jack White never plays it safe
 .\nWith so many iconic rock songs under his name\, many would have settled
  the course. Yet White stubbornly keeps going against the grain as a sonic
  iconoclast\, tender of timeless songcraft and label owner of Third Man Re
 cords. Qualities steadily upheld in his own extensive solo output\, and in
  bands like The White Stripes\, The Dead Weather and The Raconteurs. And e
 veryone knows about it.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a2fb4c192358590d@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T133000Z
DTEND:20260611T141500Z
SUMMARY:NewDad
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Irish indie rock phenoms\n\nKids are rummaging parents’ music
  collections\, and subsequently starting cool new bands. You can add Irish
  indie rockers NewDad to that crop.Those tried and true sounds clashing he
 ad on with restless\, radical youth makes for something unspeakbly fresh. 
 NewDad's gloomy but playful concoction of grunge\, shoegaze and dream pop 
 is likewise brimming with brilliant melodies and a lightning-in-the bottle
  energy that's hard to match.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-7da35ab9d90e468f@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T151500Z
DTEND:20260611T161500Z
SUMMARY:Sudan Archives
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Gadget girl of forward-thinking pop\, dance and R&B\n\nEvery ti
 me Sudan Archives releases a new album\, it feels like we’re shown a gli
 mpse into the future of pop music itself.\nSudan’s latest long player TH
 E BPM ups the tempo from her pop\, R&B and hip-hop abstractions\, taking d
 eep inspiration from the legendary club scenes in Detroit\, New Jersey and
  Chicago. A quest to get in sync with her inner rhythm: somewhere between 
 the spiritual and the silly\, cherrypicking elements from the gospel as re
 adily as from cyberpunk.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-8ade04d055bc65da@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T171500Z
DTEND:20260611T181500Z
SUMMARY:Amaarae
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Transatlantic R&B & pop marvel\n\nAmaarae is a self-proclaimed 
 warrior princess of radical dancefloor bangers.\nBorn in the Bronx with Gh
 anaian roots\, this fast-rising producer\, songwriter and vocalist pens sw
 eltering tracks that are both ethereal and club-ready. Amaarae's transatla
 ntic R&B/Afrobeat hybrid pop is rooted in highlife\, baile funk and dance 
 music\, yet bares a non-conformist\, playful streak that trail blazes stra
 ight into the future.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9c5cb036e6d3d2e4@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T191500Z
DTEND:20260611T201500Z
SUMMARY:Blood Incantation
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:One of death metal's most visionary bands\n\nIn their own words
 \, death metal behemoths Blood Incantation make mystical music for mystica
 l people.\nAnd for brevity's sake\, this is all true. For these guys are a
 ctual wizards in real life\, fusing elements like psychedelic rock\, black
  metal\, sci-fi\, ambient\, and prog into something\, well\, unlike anythi
 ng else. Weird? Transcendental? Influential to a whole new generation of m
 etal bands? Blood Incantation checks off all those boxes and then some. Th
 is will be no mere concert: this will be an odyssey of the gravest kind.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d98008bc3c383ca5@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T220000Z
DTEND:20260611T230000Z
SUMMARY:Mula
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Narco pop superstar\n\nMula and his intoxicating genre-blending
  narco pop blueprint are changing the entire Dutch rap game.If you walk th
 e streets at night in any city\, you hear all sorts of music fading in and
  out of each other – indie\, pop\, psychedelic rock\, rap\, reggaeton. M
 ula adopted this miscellany to his own kitchen sink hip-hop tales and kabo
 om\, suddenly\, he became one of the most revitalising performers of the L
 ow Countries. And we’re sure glad to have Mula back in Hilvarenbeek.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-358bad5f0b596f01@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T123000Z
DTEND:20260611T133000Z
SUMMARY:Ão
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Warm-blooded & ethereal electronic pop\n\nBelgian formation Ão
 ’s debut album ‘Ao Mar’ is Portuguese for ‘to the sea’.It’s ha
 rd to imagine a more apt way to describe their enchanting\, constantly unf
 urling music. Ão’s songs are texturally rich odysseys where electronic 
 music\, dream pop\, saudade\, ambient folk and neojazz constantly shape-sh
 ift: habitually in the most surprising\, emotionally resonant ways.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-028642517893d705@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T141500Z
DTEND:20260611T150000Z
SUMMARY:Leoniden
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Meteoric indie-punk anthems\n\nSentimentality becomes the most 
 epic of quests with German indie-punk outfit Leoniden: anthems crammed wit
 h pure-hearted\, euphoric adrenaline. Such punching-the-air fanfare needs 
 an equally powerful foil\, which arrives in the shape of disarmingly frank
 \, unpolished lyricism\, bringing a depth and nuance that underpins the gr
 oup's hard-hitting sound. Leoniden is a no-holds-barred\, no-compromise\, 
 leaving-it-all-on-the-floor operation\, and we can never have enough bands
  like this.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-54d81d399c223aae@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T160000Z
DTEND:20260611T170000Z
SUMMARY:MAVI
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Rap spirituals of a different caliber\n\nMavi has become a gene
 rational voice of hip-hop's blossoming underground.\nIn both style and sub
 stance\, the Charlotte-born rapper has truly proven himself in a league of
  his own: impressionistic\, ambitious\, experimental and community driven.
  It has put two modern classics\, Laughing so Hard\, it Hurts (2022) and i
 ts mirage-like follow-up\, shadowbox (2024)\, on the map. Indeed\, the sky
  is in Mavi’s future… and the very limit of what he can achieve.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d6c42a16a7d025c8@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T180000Z
DTEND:20260611T190000Z
SUMMARY:Model/Actriz
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:New York-based industrial-glam powerhouse\n\nSwans\, Sonic Yout
 h\, the whole no wave movement – New York has always been fertile ground
  for loud music\, and Model/Actriz are enjoying the buffet.This band bring
 s a different type of flair to the fore: have you ever imagined Gomez Adda
 ms fronting Nine Inch Nails\, or Marc Almond featuring on a Gilla Band alb
 um? The mix of deafening noise and vaudevillian charm make Model/Actriz im
 possible to resist: their shows trigger a fundamental need for pure cathar
 sis.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f11d9c6963ed9b66@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T200000Z
DTEND:20260611T210000Z
SUMMARY:Ata Kak
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Infectious Afrobeats cult hero\n\nAta Kak’s rise as cult phen
 omenon shows us the power of Doing It Yourself – how it can cultivate so
 me completely original pop music. Yaw Atta-Owusu knew he liked reggae musi
 c\, he liked funk\, he liked Ghanaian high life music\, and he liked Grand
 master Flash. But why pick just one? With the necessary recording equipmen
 t\, his signature Twi flow and an unblemished zest for life\, Ata Kak’s 
 legendary LP Obaa Sima became a global grassroots success. And we're still
  dancing feverishly to its tunes today.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-6bb7be3751748e63@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T214500Z
DTEND:20260611T224500Z
SUMMARY:MEROL
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Dutch pop's Most Entertaining Role Model\n\nAs the pre-eminent 
 risk taker within the Dutch mainstream\, you can always count on MEROL fea
 rlessly plunge into the deepest end.The imagery of a shark – the creatur
 e she depicts on latest LP Naar De Haaien & Weer Terug – makes a lot of 
 sense: MEROL can breach the surface with razor-sharp\, risque EDM bangers\
 , but also express the introspective struggle below with layered pop gems.
  Both on stage and on her records\, fun\, danger and vulnerability are MER
 OL's favorite bedfellows.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-21f529d447074ad0@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T230000Z
DTEND:20260612T003000Z
SUMMARY:Indie Gloria
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Indie gems served by the barrel\n\nIndie Gloria is that heartfe
 lt embrace with your friends when you are surprised by a brilliant track.\
 nThis Hague-based duo\, consisting of Wouter Andeweg and Abel Vlaanderen\,
  shares a love for innovative dance\, indie\, and pop. Together\, they del
 iver an energetic set where they effortlessly play Four Tet\, Fontaines D.
 C.\, and Charli XCX in one breath.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-20ca1e013c3a42d2@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T120000Z
DTEND:20260611T150000Z
SUMMARY:DJ St. Paul
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:The Floor manager who lets it all happen\n\nDJ St. Paul aka the
  pundit behind Pop-O-Matic\, aka the honcho of Let It Happen\, aka the chi
 ef facilitator of Best Kept Secret's The Floor.Paul isn’t a floor manage
 r like those at normal work environments\; it’s all play in his book. Ev
 ery year he invites an uncanny list of guests from all corners and crevice
 s of the music world – blasting the biggest hits\, the most vital niches
  & subcultures\, the juiciest of deep cuts\, and everything inbetween at T
 he Floor. It’s quite literally all hands on deck when St. Paul’s your 
 host – an exploration of pure dance-floor euphoria in all its vast devia
 tions. An individual eternally ready for both the moment and the sound.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-2e20243e1751ffe7@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T150000Z
DTEND:20260611T160000Z
SUMMARY:Rimini Express (Vinyl Only Italo Set)
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:A devoted missionary for all things Italo\n\nNo fake moustaches
  or other indulging clichés on this guy’s body. Rimini Express carries 
 the Italo experience in his heart.\nIn the club\, with his radioshow or ev
 en via lectures\, the gingerly rising DJ is spreading his obsessive passio
 n for the depths of Italy’s ever more popular soundtrack. Strictly on vi
 nyl of course. Hop on the Rimini Express and try his love beat by beat.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
