UID:best-kept-secret-2026-2f633301e1bf6039@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T131500Z
DTEND:20260611T140000Z
SUMMARY:Croíthe
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Darkly romantic noise rock up-and-comers\n\nFontaines D.C.\, Th
 e Murder Capital\, Sprints\, Gurriers... and now\, Croíthe appear to be t
 he next to grab the baton. Great bands from Ireland seem sprout to the sur
 face just about every second these days: Croíthe bring that darkly romant
 ic\, prowling goth/shoegaze sensibility that will make fans of Bauhaus\, S
 isters Of Mercy and fellow Dublin-dwellers Just Mustard salivate.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a022ca43f33828e7@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T144500Z
DTEND:20260611T153000Z
SUMMARY:Pacifica
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Pure-hearted\, cheeky garage bangers\n\nA good riff\, a good ho
 ok and pure attitude: Buenos Aires garage-duo Pacifica are the definition 
 of no-frills cool.\nIndeed\, the winds definitely worked in Inés Adam and
  Martina Nintzel’s favour when a random internet commenter – and a mut
 ual appreciation for The Strokes – brought them together to form a band.
  The duo’s combined brilliance forges earworms that illustrate the messi
 er aspects of being young\, in love with life and coping with all the trea
 cherous growing pains that come with that. Pacifica are fun\, frantic and 
 utterly in-your-face.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-bcc24d07f3338f9b@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T161500Z
DTEND:20260611T170000Z
SUMMARY:Elmer
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Non-conformist fusion of Dutch rap and theatre\n\nUnder her rap
 per alter ego Elmer\, Dutch artist & producer Merel Pauw is a bona fide in
 terloper\, causing shockwaves within the discourse of theatre\, hip-hop an
 d pop.On debut album ‘platland’\, Elmer forges a vital and off-beat mi
 x of rap\, techno and cabaret: a musical journey swerving between playful 
 agitation and deep reflection. Elmer’s shows celebrate the weird and pul
 l against the threads of gender roles and normative thinking with inventiv
 e (musical) contrasts and witty lyricism. A true cultural tour-de-force.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9f7aeb2d96ec2632@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T174500Z
DTEND:20260611T183000Z
SUMMARY:Shady Nasty
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Fiery mix of hip-hop\, post-punk and electronics\n\nAdd a Fred 
 again.. to your list of fans\, and things suddenly travel at warp-speed. T
 his is exactly what happened to Australian act Shady Nasty.Frankly\, the e
 nthusiasm is entirely justified\, because Shady Nasty's sound is as immedi
 ately bewitching as its tricky to define. Their adventurous productions sl
 ither in that liminal space between post-punk and hip-hop\, with lyrics ca
 ndidly channeling the everyday grind. Shady Nasty is already a cross-cultu
 ral marvel to truly reckon with.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5cedca1bd8c679c9@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T191500Z
DTEND:20260611T200000Z
SUMMARY:Militarie Gun
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Post-hardcore of poetic honesty\n\nMilitarie Gun convert hard l
 uck tales into rousing\, satisfying releases like few other bands can.Foun
 ded by frontman Ian Shelton\, these American post-hardcore innovators rest
 lessly seek out small blades of hope and vulnerability peering out from th
 e hard-paved realities. They show that revolt isn’t just about shouting 
 at the masses: illustrating one’s daily concerns and struggles can strik
 e just as urgently.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a54422f840048aaa@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T204500Z
DTEND:20260611T213000Z
SUMMARY:Swordes
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Underground electro/hyperpop nonconformist\n\nCutting her teeth
  within the Brooklyn warehouse rave scenes\, Swordes makes - in her own wo
 rds - human music for humans.\nThe result is a headstrong hardware-only ap
 proach to composing\, producing and performing\, juxtaposing cutesy hyper 
 pop elements with gloomier\, gnarlier 80s electronica influences. Bubblegu
 m\, rainbows\, fire and gasoline: Swordes brings a club-friendly pop exorc
 ism that pierces like the sharpest of blades.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f766fbe73c5e6852@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T221500Z
DTEND:20260611T230000Z
SUMMARY:supermodel*
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Catchy & distinctive genre-blender with DIY-ethos\n\nUS artist 
 Frankie Beanie's ground rules for his solo-project supermodel*: don't try 
 and be cool\, nick everything\, keep it lowercase\, don't overthink\, alwa
 ys talk about fight club. It translates to fun\, thrifty songs that channe
 l MF Doom as much as LCD Soundsystem. Beanie’s frank\, observational lyr
 ics draw partly from his experiences as an American living in the UK\, com
 plete with Be Kind Rewind-esque homages to Jamiroquai and Fatboy Slim. Eff
 ortlessly charming\, unpolished and yeah\, actually pretty damn cool.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5016e14f35250db9@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T230000Z
DTEND:20260612T020000Z
SUMMARY:Tramhaus (DJ Set)
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Casbah DJ set by Rotterdam's rowdiest band\n\nTramhaus's snowba
 lling success from Rotterdam's lively underground to one of Europe's great
 est livebands has been downright inspiring.\nAnd in that journey\, its mem
 bers have amassed a great deal of inspiration themselves from music both l
 ocal and far across the world. A breadth of influences and favorites disti
 lled down to an energetic DJ set at their familiar stomping grounds The Ca
 sbah.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-81faf16e436ac51c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T143000Z
DTEND:20260611T145000Z
SUMMARY:Humanistisch Verbond - Analoog Algoritme
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Inzicht in je eigen fabrieksinstellingen\n\nWat stuurt jouw lev
 en\, zonder dat je het doorhebt? In deze scherpe maar toegankelijke cabare
 tshow ontdek je hoe beelden\, verwachtingen en gewoontes zich ongemerkt ne
 stelen in jouw leven.\nMet humor en herkenbare voorbeelden laat de cabaret
 ier zien hoe deze ‘offline algoritmes’ jouw keuzes\, relaties en drome
 n beïnvloeden. Een uitnodiging om even uit de automatische piloot te stap
 pen\, te lachen om je eigen patronen en te verbeelden hoe het ook anders k
 an.\nPlease note: This program item is in Dutch
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-6a1df0c2178f5f90@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T150000Z
DTEND:20260611T154500Z
SUMMARY:Reality Check - De sappigste spoedcursus B&B Vol Liefde
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Met doorgewinterde reality-tv experts Eva\, Timo en Dook.\n\nNo
 g even en dan begint het favoriete reality-programma van Nederland weer: B
 &B vol Liefde. Hosts Eva\, Timo en Dook zijn doorgewinterde reality-tv exp
 erts en grote fans van dit spraakmakende programma en bespreken in hun pod
 cast elke aflevering. Op Best Kept Secret stomen we je klaar voor een nieu
 w seizoen B&B vol Liefde. Aan de hand van de nieuwe en oude kandidaten bli
 kken we vooruit en kijken we terug op 5 jaar B&B Vol Liefde. En voorspelle
 n we welke kandidaat dit seizoen de publieksfavoriet gaat worden. Yamas!\n
 Please note: This program item is in Dutch.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5b6a0cb3f4c7df98@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T160000Z
DTEND:20260611T162000Z
SUMMARY:Humanistisch Verbond - Analoog Algoritme
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Inzicht in je eigen fabrieksinstellingen\n\nWat stuurt jouw lev
 en\, zonder dat je het doorhebt? In deze scherpe maar toegankelijke cabare
 tshow ontdek je hoe beelden\, verwachtingen en gewoontes zich ongemerkt ne
 stelen in jouw leven.\nMet humor en herkenbare voorbeelden laat de cabaret
 ier zien hoe deze ‘offline algoritmes’ jouw keuzes\, relaties en drome
 n beïnvloeden. Een uitnodiging om even uit de automatische piloot te stap
 pen\, te lachen om je eigen patronen en te verbeelden hoe het ook anders k
 an.\nPlease note: This program item is in Dutch
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-21b9bf45771ce533@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T163000Z
DTEND:20260611T180000Z
SUMMARY:Aram Mukanay B2B Deodaat
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Percussive B2B from two of the best groove-welders around\n\nAr
 am Mukanay's fixation on 80's grooves and Deodaat's love for fringe latin 
 sounds make pretty effective bedfellows.\nAram will string together dubby 
 disco\, soulful house and 80s boogie in his signature smooth\, free spirit
 ed way\; then it's up to Deodaat to take the baton and unleash a percussiv
 e assault that feels both homely and heady. Snap\, crackle and pop!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-04063f02f911f6f1@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T180000Z
DTEND:20260611T200000Z
SUMMARY:KINETIKS
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Best friends breaking the limits of house music itself\n\nBente
  and Rozemarijn\, aka KINETIKS\, have built their friendship on a dispropo
 rtionate love for house music in its many vast shapes.\nIt proved to be a 
 pivotal shared interest\, because KINETIKS have done right by their name w
 ith notorious sets that stretch the limits of house off the wazoo. Rebelli
 ous\, resonant and always up to stir the pot and break open a brand new la
 ne: KINETIKS are indeed a true delight.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a96d67e351d9ff91@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T200000Z
DTEND:20260611T220000Z
SUMMARY:Mavochi b2b DIEDE
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:A b2b exploring the outer realms of house music\n\nMavochi and 
 DIEDE both take house to captivating new wavelengths\, in their own distin
 ct ways.\nMavochi are Amersfoort’s most beloved house music mavens\; the
  duo of Lars and Tommie are known for impeccable selections\, smooth mixin
 g skills and loose atmosphere. DIEDE’s specialty is minimal house and du
 b inflected dance music\, breezy vibes through and through. Both acts join
  forces to explore house music’s hypnotic and propulsive qualities.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-cb3a71b985aabf28@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T220000Z
DTEND:20260612T000000Z
SUMMARY:Doppelgang
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Twins with a taste for house\, acid & ravey disco\n\nIt takes t
 wo to make a thing go right\; the twins Sander and Maurice de Graaf have b
 een a mainstay in the Dutch club and festival scenes since 2012.\nWith a n
 atural gift for fun hijinks\, colorful fashion and frantic beats\, Doppelg
 ang pour their contagious charisma into all the records they play: from de
 ephouse to disco. An experience oftentimes levelled up by an avid courting
  of kitsch\, drag queen theatre and the funkiest of dance routines.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f2538fb37434c166@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T000000Z
DTEND:20260612T020000Z
SUMMARY:Sedef Adasï
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:All-embracing dance floor journeys between acid & pop\n\nAs one
  of Germany’s top selectors and DJs\, Sedef Adasï blends proto-disco\, 
 techno\, acid house and vintage pop with proficient\, spectacular sets.\nS
 edef brings an exciting push and pull between fringe sounds and pop euphor
 ia\, naturally inviting different (sub)cultures to interact in thrilling w
 ays. Places like Munich’s BLITZ club and Berlin’s Panorama Bar can cer
 tainly attest\, and having one of Boiler Room's most legendary sets to you
 r name seals that deal pretty soundly.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-57b87f57833def22@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T140000Z
DTEND:20260611T170000Z
SUMMARY:Fada Jep
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:A leading light in soundsystem movements\n\nSince the early 90s
 \, Fada Jep has been a leading authority in reggae\, dancehall\, dub and a
 ll affiliated musical movements.\nAs a selector\, DJ and label owner\, Jep
  Verhorevoort has sent positive vibrations out at every block party\, club
  and festival you can think of. Fada Jep's passion for his craft is self-e
 vident in his sets and runs as deep as the bass will take him.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-b0987d4334fc8ccd@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T170000Z
DTEND:20260611T190000Z
SUMMARY:Bibtiana: music from Île Maurice
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Top Notch/Noah's Ark member & DJ goes knee-deep into Mauritian 
 Seggae\n\nMusic isn't just for bread and circuses\; it's a priceless form 
 of resistance. Seggae is a prime example of this.\nSeggae music derives fr
 om Sega\, the traditional folk music from Mauritius. This vibrant strand o
 f dance music was invented in the 80s by Mauritian artist Kaya\; music cre
 ated for the uprising Creole people in Mauritius. Bibtiana will give Segga
 e a vital modern twist with this blistering DJ set.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e65a4ff7404dab9e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T190000Z
DTEND:20260611T210000Z
SUMMARY:DJ Tracksuit
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Dedicated digger of Afro-Caribbean sounds\n\nDJ Tracksuit has w
 orked out the science behind the soiree-making: a true student of the game
  with a nose for vibrant Afro-Caribbean sounds.\nMaking people dance and t
 elling a story behind the decks are indeed one and the same for this Belgi
 an connoisseur and collector. Knowing is half the battle for Timothy Vande
 rputte\; the other half is spinning the dancefloor dizzy with a a cultural
 ly rich\, inclusive experience that engages both body and soul.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-348ff8ba9995efe9@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T210000Z
DTEND:20260611T223000Z
SUMMARY:Cami Layé Okún
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Infectious Cuban & Afro-Latin sounds\n\nCuban DJ\, selector\, a
 rtist and radio host Cami Layé Okún conjures up a distinct mix of Cuban 
 disco\, Afro-Caribbean rarities\, and Amazonian funk.\nOther than having a
 n impeccable nose for the best hidden gems\, Cami exemplifies the joy of b
 eing a certified crate digger\; chasing those elusive jams that can unlock
  new windows in body and soul. Cami’s sets are adventurous\, infectious 
 and always tell a bigger story.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-741c02fa6a833d70@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260611T223000Z
DTEND:20260612T000000Z
SUMMARY:Susobrino
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Vibrant clash of Latin American jams & electronica\n\nBolivia-b
 orn\, Brussels-based artist Susobrino is deeply connected to Latin America
 ’s rich soundscapes.\nBoth his live sets and DJ sets are driven by rhyth
 m\, emotion\, curiosity and exploration\, blending acoustic instruments an
 d electronics into something grounded\, funny and unpredictable. 'SU SO BR
 I NO' contains boleros\, cumbia\, club music\, folklore\, and film scores 
 all colliding and manifesting into Susobrino’s warped wizardry.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-fd51c82ae876aba9@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T120000Z
DTEND:20260612T124500Z
SUMMARY:Naïka
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Rising Transatlantic pop and R&B icon\n\nA child of overlapping
  different cultures\, languages and heritages\, Naïka is redefining the g
 lobal pop star with unrivalled aplomb.\nThe rising artist’s long awaited
  debut LP ECLESIA does exactly what its title promised: reconciling Naïka
 ’s Haitian\, French and American roots to create a warm-blooded\, forwar
 d thinking brand of Transatlantic pop. Having lead a nomadic young life\, 
 Naïka's music carves out a genre-blending sanctuary of her very own makin
 g.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-db578b8e2c10bb0c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T134500Z
DTEND:20260612T144500Z
SUMMARY:Sef
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:One of Dutch rap's chief voices\n\nYou can always count on Dutc
 h-Moroccan artist Sef to capture the moment urgently and sincerely.\nWith 
 his deeply impressive performances on big festival stages last summer\, an
 d a sold-out club tour still fresh in our minds\, Sef has solidified himse
 lf as one of Dutch rap’s leading lights. From his beloved hip-hop staple
  De Leven to latest LP lieve monsters – a dark but danceable tale of col
 lective despair – Yousef Gnaoui enters Best Kept Secret with a surplus o
 f stories\, stirring energy and moments that’ll stick with you.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a6436ba05f693729@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T154500Z
DTEND:20260612T164500Z
SUMMARY:Hayley Williams
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Paramore icon & eclectic pop star\n\nFrom fronting pop punk ico
 ns Paramore to spearheading an illustrious solo career\, Hayley Williams's
  artistic walk of life is both singular and inspiring.Williams influenced 
 a whole generation of stars\, from Billie Eilish to Olivia Rodrigo – and
  the damnedest thing happened: those artists reinvigorated her work in ret
 urn. The 17 song release Ego Death At a Bachelorette Party is as multi-fac
 eted and free spirited as pop music gets – plus a rare shining example o
 f a grassroots and community-driven project on a mainstream level. This is
  why Hayley Williams is truly our favorite band.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f376a960da2c43e7@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T174500Z
DTEND:20260612T184500Z
SUMMARY:Wolf Alice
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Resonant UK alt rock sensation\n\nBritains biggest indie rock b
 and Wolf Alice keeps unpacking and unraveling.\nTheir latest LP The Cleari
 ng luxuriates in aspects of some of rock music’s greatest – the melodi
 c genius of Fleetwood Mac\, the glam rock strut of T-Rex\, the technicolor
  exuberance of ELO. Wolf Alice have plenty of classics to call their own: 
 how many songs capture both the devastation and thrill of falling in love 
 better than “Don’t Delete The Kisses”? Best Kept Secret has felt thi
 s thrill many times before. Safe to say\, that third post-show dip in the 
 lake’s a charm.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-21b4bcaec223fd85@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T200000Z
DTEND:20260612T220000Z
SUMMARY:Nick Cave & The Bad Seeds
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Legendary songsmith of darkness and devotion\n\nFew artists enc
 ompass the profound breadth of human emotion quite like Nick Cave and his 
 Bad Seeds.\nMenacing\, majestic and often-times touching the divine\, they
  have one of the most acclaimed back catalogs around. Nick Cave's ability 
 to veer from blackened goth punk sermons to a tender-hearted gospel ballad
  is no longer a secret so well kept. After a thunderous show in 2022\, Nic
 k Cave and the Bad Seeds return to Hilvarenbeek with hymns of faith\, hope
  and carnage both new and old.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f8beb43b47497f38@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T100000Z
DTEND:20260612T104500Z
SUMMARY:mark william lewis
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Resonant & cinematic alternative folk\n\nWithin the dusky\, noc
 turnal songs of mark william lewis you can untangle head and heart at your
  own desired pace.Blessed with a deep baritone and a talent for painting s
 cenes with through minimal means\, it’s no wonder art house film giant A
 24 decided to ink the UK songwriter to a record deal. There is a gothic my
 stery lingering in lewis's songs\, a love for electronic music\, rap\, gri
 me and indie rock permeating through. An artist whose romanticism and flui
 dity are understated\, yet undeniably magnetic.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-3218e20c10ad7dd6@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T111500Z
DTEND:20260612T120000Z
SUMMARY:Hiqpy
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Hot-blooded shoegaze/alt-rock sensation\n\nAt a blazing pace\, 
 Amsterdam quartet Hiqpy has already mastered all the intangibles of a grea
 t rock band.\nThe band has cultivated a penchant for scene stealing stage 
 dramatics and scorching melodies\, executed with more bluster and charisma
  than you can throw a stick at. With long awaited debut LP Slow Death Of A
  Good Girl unleashed in the world\, Hiqpy are ready to up the ante for the
 ir second Best Kept Secret-stint.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-2e45f0a0f982b534@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T124500Z
DTEND:20260612T134500Z
SUMMARY:Weval (live)
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Tasteful electro-acoustic dream weavers\n\nThere's an immense c
 are this Dutch duo put into their chosen craft – and a surrender to one
 ’s deepest listening instincts.Those two methods are part of the Weval m
 agic – the studious tinkering vs. the spontaneity of live instrumentatio
 n\, until that sweet innuendo between the artificial and the organic is ac
 hieved. Through headphones and across the dancefloors\, Weval remains an e
 ver-sublime and satisfying operation\, renowned across all corners of the 
 world.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-0cfe250eaaa4f302@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T144500Z
DTEND:20260612T154500Z
SUMMARY:Aldous Harding
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Chameleon-like alt folk siren\n\nAldous Harding is one of those
  rare shapeshifting artists that comes along every so often.Sometimes in t
 he very same song\, she can be theatrical\, comedic\, soothing and frighte
 ning in a heartbeat – leaving audiences catching their breath on what co
 uld happen next. Since Harding's 2019 breakthrough album Designer\, her my
 stique and magnetism only seems to have grown\, writing songs that often c
 apture the phenomena inside the gaps of living we tend to overlook.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a27f4b671fdddf11@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T164500Z
DTEND:20260612T174500Z
SUMMARY:Nation of Language
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:New York synth pop torchbearers\n\nAfter Kraftwerk\, New Order\
 , and LCD Soundsystem passed the baton\, now Nation Of Language upholds th
 e continuum of new wave and synth pop greatness.The New York band's latest
  LP Dance Called Memory\, poetically enough\, grasps retroactively with ho
 w one wishes to be remembered\, its songs emphasising physicality\, imperm
 anence and flaw over artifice and perfection. We're pleased to bring Natio
 n Of Language back to Best Kept Secret's lakeside scenery.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-fec3b6d43327ff83@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T184500Z
DTEND:20260612T194500Z
SUMMARY:Tramhaus
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Rotterdam-based punk rock collossus\n\nAt a blistering pace\, T
 ramhaus snowballed from Rotterdam’s latest post-punk curiosity to one of
  Europe’s greatest rock bands.And with two legendary shows at Best Kept 
 Secret already under the group's belt\, it makes perfect sense to invite t
 hem back for another noisy merry-go-round. Beneath all those powerhouse ri
 ffs\, blunt force trauma\, and indefatigable DIY spirit\, Tramhaus are a b
 and with a big beating heart\, and a special knack for making audiences fe
 el present\, seen and loved.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5e6587a744c7c1e2@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T220000Z
DTEND:20260612T230000Z
SUMMARY:Job Jobse
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Amsterdam's most notorious club culture omnivore\n\nFrom gravey
 ard shifts at legendary club Trouw to becoming one of the most renowned DJ
 s worldwide\, Job Jobse’s life is a metronome-driven pipe dream.\nThroug
 h all of his dizzying success\, Jobse's love for the game and the geeking 
 out behind the booth never ever wavers. The reason why this guy is so in-d
 emand is obvious: Job can do any type of DJ set that fits the imagination\
 , from euphoria bursting trance to slow-building house beats.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-574d95cd8609e39c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T110000Z
DTEND:20260612T114500Z
SUMMARY:Madra Salach
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Enchanting electronica-tinged folk\n\nDublin sextet Madra Salac
 h write gripping electronica-infused folk\, scrambling tradition with rein
 vention in baffling ways.\nOriginally playing in various groups\, their sh
 ared love of the Irish traditional canon led to a spontaneous band playing
  in pubs. Inspired by the growing Irish experimental folk scene\, Madra Sa
 lach’s songs\, while thematically modern\, are written with a voice that
  could have originated at any point in the last century.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-27116e206ab5a9a2@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T123000Z
DTEND:20260612T131500Z
SUMMARY:Maddie Ashman
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Eerie and beautiful\, Maddie Ashman's music sounds like folk so
 ngs gone through the digital wood chipper\, glued together like a strange 
 collage.\nThe UK composer\, performer\, and songwriterr often explores the
  connections between sound and the environment. As a result\, her music fe
 els emblematic to the desire to escape technology’s clutches\, and the y
 earning for something more human and imperfect.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-73eca1b99f7cacde@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T140000Z
DTEND:20260612T144500Z
SUMMARY:Sorry
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Indie rock with a novelistic bite\n\nSorry imbue their cinemati
 c & angular indie rock with the storytelling prowess of a distinguished no
 velist.Seedy tales of the city\, the taboos of love and sex\, the horrors 
 of post-modern living – Asha Lorenz and Louis O’ Bryen intend to unpac
 k it all. The band’s fantastic latest LP Cosplay unmasks both their inne
 r tensions and the pretenses of the outside world.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ec19a8abee4a3583@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T154500Z
DTEND:20260612T163000Z
SUMMARY:Radio Free Alice
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Hazy post-punk and new wave risers\n\nWith their layered atmosp
 heric songs\, Aussie new wave/post-punk group Radio Free Alice sound nosta
 lgic and fresh at once.\nThere’s a misty\, dream-like quality to the ban
 d\, inviting that deja vu feeling that you heard their songs before\, long
  ago. We hear the honed song craft of The Smiths and Orange Juice\, combin
 ed with the dark brooding atmospherics of a Joy Division and Interpol. Ind
 eed\, Radio Free Alice have all the elements of a band to cherish for deca
 des to come.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-c4766740825ebbf4@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T173000Z
DTEND:20260612T183000Z
SUMMARY:Tropical Fuck Storm
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Noisy blues punk abomination\n\nImagine all of your favorite ro
 ck bands melted down into some sort of stenchy primordial soup\, only to r
 ise and reform.\nThat\, in a nutshell\, is would be Tropical Fuck Storm. S
 ince the year 2017\, these rock veterans have torn up the rulebook of what
  constitutes as guitar music in the most mind-blowing ways. Through sickne
 ss\, strife\, and squalls of noise – Tropical Fuck Storm is as resilient
  to apocalyptic occurences as the famous cockroach.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-835624707ec3a587@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T193000Z
DTEND:20260612T203000Z
SUMMARY:The Zawose Queens
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Rapturous Gogo spirituals\n\nTanzania's Zawose Queens channel v
 ibrations of the ancestors through their rapturous polyphonic singing. As 
 the daughter and granddaughter of the legendary Dr. Hukwe Zawose\, Leah an
 d Pendo are ushering in the family tradition as its first female practitio
 ners. Their fusion of the Gogo music and modern-day electronics expresses 
 a deep connection towards nature\, to ceremony and to ritual: music teemin
 g with unshakable spirit and fire.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e7eac73ddcc2363e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T213000Z
DTEND:20260612T223000Z
SUMMARY:BCUC
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Fast & furious Afro-psych jams\n\nThe Afropsychedelic pounce of
  Bantu Continua Uhuru Consciousness screams with a zealous\, ceremonial sp
 irit.BCUC's formula seems so simple when you break it down: bass\, drums\,
  percussion\, voice chants all conspiring to spark frantic\, joyous moveme
 nt. And the Soweto\, South-Africa based collective does this better than a
 nyone: this is music awakened from ancient lineage\, yet visionary\, loud 
 and transcending convention of what a band can be.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-434965af5930716d@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T233000Z
DTEND:20260613T020000Z
SUMMARY:Lucky Done Gone
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Genre-blending DJ who brings that rare dancefloor euphoria\n\nI
 f one is forced to narrow down a Lucky Done Gone DJ set in just two terms\
 , it would be ‘carefree and contagious’.\nAnd if a third signifier can
  be cheated in\, you can add 'genre-blurring' to the mix as well. Like a m
 agpie who loves all shiny things\, Lucky cherrypicks his favorite elements
  from basically any imaginable club movement – be it house\, 90s techno\
 , 00s trance\, old school or new school – and mold it into something fre
 sh and euphoria-inducing. A master at his craft\, passion and proficiency 
 personified.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-4d96598c097d9f34@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T100000Z
DTEND:20260612T113000Z
SUMMARY:DJ St. Paul
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:The Floor manager who lets it all happen\n\nDJ St. Paul aka the
  pundit behind Pop-O-Matic\, aka the honcho of Let It Happen\, aka the chi
 ef facilitator of Best Kept Secret's The Floor.Paul isn’t a floor manage
 r like those at normal work environments\; it’s all play in his book. Ev
 ery year he invites an uncanny list of guests from all corners and crevice
 s of the music world – blasting the biggest hits\, the most vital niches
  & subcultures\, the juiciest of deep cuts\, and everything inbetween at T
 he Floor. It’s quite literally all hands on deck when St. Paul’s your 
 host – an exploration of pure dance-floor euphoria in all its vast devia
 tions. An individual eternally ready for both the moment and the sound.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a5643fa8cc04dc59@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T113000Z
DTEND:20260612T123000Z
SUMMARY:Katayoun
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:Collector\, radio host & DJ of Iranian music\n\nKatayoun Arian 
 is a DJ\, selector and archivist working across sounds from Iran and the w
 ider region.\nDrawing on everything from pre-revolution grooves and pop to
  trance-inducing ritual rhythms\, she builds sets that cut across borders 
 and timelines. Her work moves between deeper listening and dancefloor: it 
 is less about nostalgia\, more about the reactivation of rarities and brin
 ging together different musical worlds\, showing how music can move beyond
  boundaries.\nPhoto by: Lisa van den Berg
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
