BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-fe5edd99e1a37995@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T230000Z
DTEND:20260613T000000Z
SUMMARY:Ajuma
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:Celebrating organic sounds in a dystopian world\n\nAjuma unders
 tands the power of music to evoke emotions like no other.\nShe’s an arde
 nt music lover with an ear for the surprising and obscure. Wherever she go
 es\, she leaves behind a warm and inviting atmosphere on the dancefloor\, 
 blending together genres into a recognizable sound that is always soulful 
 oriented. She moves between deeper and uplifting moments\, at the heart of
  her sound lies an endless love for that (raw) percussion. Ajuma is openin
 g borders. Surrender your love!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-38a7a0d58511a923@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T000000Z
DTEND:20260613T020000Z
SUMMARY:The Great Indie Dance Bake Off (DJ St. Paul B2B Riptide)
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:Gifted producer and passionate Floor-manager breaking down the 
 history of indie dance\n\nI was there! Producer Riptide and host DJ St. Pa
 ul present the premiere of The Great Indie Dance Bake Off.The finale of Sa
 turday night at the Floor has a tradition of memorable B2Bs. This time pro
 ducer Riptide (his Rug Busters remix for Personal Trainer is what Charli w
 ould call a modern-day club classic) and DJ St. Paul will take you on an c
 olourful journey through the history of indie dance. Travelling from Talki
 ng Heads via Gorillaz to Decius and Robyn. Premiering some of their own ed
 its of favourite tracks. Oh\, if I could see all my friends tonight!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-15bac75f0c6c34ca@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T101500Z
DTEND:20260612T110000Z
SUMMARY:Bruno Berle
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Supple polaroid filter latin pop\n\nThis Brazilian composer and
  troubadour writes honeysweet latin pop brimming with deft arrangements.\n
 From accounts of people who have been to Brazil\, it does seem like time w
 orks differently over there. Bruno Berle’s warm-blooded pop affirms this
  notion all the more. Carefree\, soft around the edges and unhurried\, Ber
 le’s tunes embrace you with the kind of affinity of a home-cooked meal. 
 For you lovers out there\, Bruno’s set at Best Kept would be good time t
 o get cosy.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a7855be77ef65cf8@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T114500Z
DTEND:20260612T123000Z
SUMMARY:Any Young Mechanic
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Jangly indie pop sensation\n\nAfter breaking out with their sun
 -kissed open-the-drapes single 'Snug Barber'\, this Aussie five-piece is i
 mmediately irresistable.\nMaintaining a fine-tuned balance between jangly 
 and cinematic\, Any Young Mechanic recall Vampire Weekend or perhaps a sli
 ghtly more mellowed out Violent Femmes. They embody the comfort of a fraye
 d sweater\, with an affable\, somewhat neurotic charm.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-cd1c01ff3698ca0f@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T131500Z
DTEND:20260612T140000Z
SUMMARY:Grote Geelstaart
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Math-tastic prog-noise minions\n\nImagine Geordie Greep frontin
 g Talking Heads instead of David Byrne: that's just one wild take on the b
 affling madness of rising Dutch outfit Grote Geelstaart.\nIf music was som
 ehow a math equation unlocking the fifth dimension in space\, Grote Geelst
 aart are the kind of band to figure it out\, using odd time signatures\, r
 iffs that scream 'fuck you\, diatonic scale!'\, and a lot of sweating it o
 ut through three-piece suits. Grote Geelstaart's music will flop like fish
  out of water\, only to magically grow arms and legs on the spot: rock mus
 ic evolving in real time!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-b774e0c1d89cd865@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T144500Z
DTEND:20260612T153000Z
SUMMARY:Etta Marcus
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Layered and atmospheric indie pop\n\nLonging\, sadness\, grit\,
  and dark humour: there’s always a lot of emotions coexisting in Etta Ma
 rcus’s songs.\nThat puts the Brixton-based songsmith in a rare echelon o
 f songwriters\, namely touchstones like Fiona Apple\, Hope Sandoval\, Jeff
  Buckley and Lana del Rey (Marcus opened for the latter). She is adept at 
 bittersweet\, layered gems that reconcile the highest of highs with the lo
 west of lows.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-0b59e392e32af725@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T161500Z
DTEND:20260612T170000Z
SUMMARY:Crows
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Influential post-punk heavy-hitters\n\nThe ragged souls of Crow
 s take flight at Best Kept Secret with a top shelf slab of heavy-melodic p
 ost-punk.\nThe UK band have basically been your favorite band's favorite b
 and\; IDLES' Joe Talbot is one person who has professed how influential th
 ey were to his own group. Often pegged as brooding romantics\, Crows gigs 
 regularly unfold in spiritual\, sweaty communions. Emotional moshpits are 
 often the best\, right?
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e932fa9585cd9f6f@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T174500Z
DTEND:20260612T183000Z
SUMMARY:Midrift
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Prodigal shoegaze power trio\n\nThe kids are not only embracing
  shoegaze – they are taking it to someplace new. Midrift pepper in a bit
  of emo and pop punk to make things interesting. The path of these phenoms
  is not like some of their forebears\, toiling away with raggedy house sho
 ws at first. Frontman Gus Mehrkam created his songs in his bedroom\, uploa
 ded them on TikTok\, and bang! They became viral hits. With skirmishing si
 blings Kai and Manoa Neukermans completing the power trio\, Midrift are ju
 stly what people call 'an overnight sensation'.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-784f05ab91c4fb85@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T191500Z
DTEND:20260612T200000Z
SUMMARY:GHOSTWOMAN
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Dynamic transatlantic rock duo\n\nNo genre has been declared de
 ad more than rock\; yet the duo of GHOSTWOMAN fancies itself as fiery necr
 omancers\, reinventing its raw power all over again.Canadian Evan Uschenko
  (guitars/vocals) and Belgian Ille van Dessel (drums/percussion) began the
 ir voyage an entire ocean apart: now their collision course brings new tre
 mors in activity\, exploring rock of the psychedelic\, stoner\, garage and
  indie variety through the prism of their own infectious chemistry.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-4aee05e2e06123df@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T204500Z
DTEND:20260612T213000Z
SUMMARY:Kumo 99
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Underground hardcore/breakbeat with need for speed\n\nWith big 
 beats and an even bigger attitude\, Kumo 99 put a fresh spin on the deligh
 tfully abrasive rave nostalgia of the 90s.The Los Angeles artist duo of Am
 i Komai and Nate Donmoyer don’t play it subtle when it comes to serving 
 up a clamouring bricolage of breakbeats\, industrial and digitised hardcor
 e. Kumo 99 have toured with artists as diverse as Magdalena Bay and The Ar
 med\, showing that their explosive club anthems will crush in virtually an
 y context.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9791f062a8decb08@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T221500Z
DTEND:20260612T230000Z
SUMMARY:Dame Area
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Acidic & percussive industrial romps\n\nRemember that one Death
  Grips-lyric about having the DNA of gothic lemons? It describes Barcelona
  industrial duo Dame Area to a tee. Their sound is both abrasive and stran
 gely whimsical: hissy\, static-laden textures\, bile-drenched polyrhythms 
 and shouty vocals that sound like they've been recorded in claustrophobic 
 solitary confinement. Dame Area put a fresh and fun spin on industrial mus
 ic\, marrying 'rave' and 'ravenous' in novel\, eye-opening ways.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ce985b804b059596@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T230000Z
DTEND:20260613T000000Z
SUMMARY:MEROL (DJ Debut)
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Dutch pop's Most Entertaining Role Model\n\nA Casbah DJ set by 
 one of today’s most impactful Dutch artists.\nMEROL is dropping a brand 
 new album. 'Leve de Feeks' is punk\, a middle finger and above all a liber
 ation of the openly sexual\, outspoken woman. For her DJ debut she'll be s
 pinning the tracks that shaped her\, from riot grrrl punk to techno.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-51ddd895a6673a4f@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T000000Z
DTEND:20260613T020000Z
SUMMARY:Here's The Thing DJ Set
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Post-punk\, psych rock\, indie rock and all that goodness inbet
 ween\n\nThere's nothing quite like the squeak of an amp\, the rumble of a 
 bass\, the hiss of cymbals before things are about to get real.\nThese hea
 ds from the recurring Tilburg festival know their stuff when it comes to t
 he latest noise from the fringes. From weirdos in basements to firebrands 
 prowling the bigger stages\, the landscape of genre-pushing guitar-based m
 usic seems more diverse than ever before. Here's The Thing will bundle it 
 all into a supercharged spendour!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d936d06dc291071a@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T110000Z
DTEND:20260612T114500Z
SUMMARY:de Volkskrant - Culturele Bagage
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Wie heeft er nog (zin in) seks?\n\nCulturele bagage\, de tijdge
 est- en cultuurpodcast van de Volkskrant\, duikt met jullie het bed in.\nW
 ant: zitten we in een nieuwe seksuele revolutie? Het taboe op kinks is era
 f\, monogamie is uit de mode\, experimenteren op Feeld in. Toch hebben jon
 geren steeds later seks en kijken ze vaker porno. Hebben we nou een beter 
 seksleven of is onze seks stuk? Volkskrant-journalist Esma Linnemann bespr
 eekt het met een panel van liefdesexperts.\nPlease note: This program item
  is in Dutch
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-037f57a775e1085c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T120000Z
DTEND:20260612T124500Z
SUMMARY:De Correspondent - Rob Wijnberg
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Hoe overleven we een wereld waarin waarheid leugen is geworden?
 \n\nWe leven in waanzinnige tijden. Terwijl in de VS het fascisme oplaait 
 onder het mom van ‘ware democratie’\, nota bene een Republikein regeer
 t als een koning\, en zijn oorlogszucht wordt beloond met de FIFA Vredespr
 ijs\, wordt in Gaza genocide gepleegd om “genocide te voorkomen”. Onde
 rtussen wordt de mens dommer door kunstmatige intelligentie en zijn social
 e media de minst sociale plekken ter wereld geworden. Hoe overleven we een
  wereld waarin waarheid leugen is geworden? Rob Wijnberg\, filosoof en opr
 ichter van De Correspondent\, helpt je beide voeten op de grond te houden 
 in wereld waarin alles op z’n kop lijkt te staan.\nPlease note: This pro
 gram item is in Dutch
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d4466c006e6eb374@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T130000Z
DTEND:20260612T134500Z
SUMMARY:Zo Opgelost
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Met Anna Gimbrère\, Stefan Pop en Tex de Wit\n\nDe wereld is g
 evuld met problemen. Maar hoe lossen we dat op?\nWat moeten we met voetbal
 geweld? Hoe koop je een auto? Wat geef je iemand cadeau die je niet kent? 
 Wat doen we aan het tekort aan personeel? En hoe kom je eigenlijk op tijd?
  Geen zorgen. In Zo\, Opgelost gaan wetenschapsjournalist Anna Gimbrère e
 n comedians Tex de Wit en Stefan Pop de meest complexe onderwerpen te lijf
  en lossen het voor je op.\nPlease note: This program item is in Dutch
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-75667d85e6a83f91@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T140000Z
DTEND:20260612T144500Z
SUMMARY:De Correspondent - Rinke Verkerk
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Rinke laat zien dat de wens tot neutraliteit altijd ten gunste 
 is van de pleger van geweld.\n\nJournalist Rinke Verkerk schrijft voor De 
 Correspondent over systemen van geweld. Bij geweld zijn er drie partijen: 
 de dader\, het slachtoffer én de omstanders. De rol en de positie van de 
 omstander blijkt vaak cruciaal. Wat betekent het om getuige te zijn van ge
 weld\, ook als dit geweld zich afspeelt op verre afstand\, zoals in Gaza o
 f Iran? En welke verantwoordelijkheid brengt dat met zich mee voor omstand
 ers\, waaronder politici\, de media en journalisten? Rinke laat zien dat d
 e wens tot neutraliteit altijd ten gunste is van de pleger van geweld.\nPl
 ease note: This program item is in Dutch
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ff081903e9aba194@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T150000Z
DTEND:20260612T154500Z
SUMMARY:Alle Geschiedenis Ooit
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Alle Geschiedenis Ooit nemen je mee op een tijdreis langs de be
 ste en vreemdste feesten uit de wereldgeschiedenis.\n\nHet lijkt wel alsof
  er ieder jaar meer festivals en feesten bijkomen\, maar hoe ging dat in h
 et verleden?\nAndrea Huntjens en Thom Aalmoes van de podcast Alle Geschied
 enis Ooit nemen je mee op een tijdreis langs de beste en vreemdste feesten
  uit de wereldgeschiedenis. Van Griekse feesten tot Romeinse anti-katertip
 s en van de eerste festivals tot de gekste drankspelletjes\, en weer terug
 .\nPlease note: This program item is in Dutch
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-29ca59e2b6a683db@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T154500Z
DTEND:20260612T180000Z
SUMMARY:Guylian
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Hectic and eclectic disco & house selections\n\nMany kids colle
 ct action figures or comic books at age 8 – well\, at that age\, Guylian
  was collecting records.\nSo yeah\, that passion for disco and house runs 
 deeper than the pits of Moria. Guylian’s sets are so damn groovy\, the g
 rooves themselves seem to have new grooves coming out of them\, like growi
 ng appendages. Dynamic\, flavoursome and always in for a surprise.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-10516140717499cc@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T180000Z
DTEND:20260612T200000Z
SUMMARY:JUUL
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Genre-scrambling percussive club sounds\n\nJUUL's chronic curio
 sity for fresh club sounds has her operating on an entirely different wave
 length from her DJ peers.\nJUUL navigates across the realms of house\, UK 
 funky\, breaks\, garage and even bits of baile funk. Her love for house in
  particular runs deep\, spanning across minimal and percussive back to 90s
  and soulful. Each set keeps you on your tippy toes\, with always a distin
 ctively uplifting\, groovy base hooverin' you back in.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9e8662488e9e902c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T200000Z
DTEND:20260612T220000Z
SUMMARY:OG Karin
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Raw\, rhythmic genre-blending beats\n\nOG Karin’s DJ sets bri
 m with bombshell shifts and wild tempo changes\, and audiences have quickl
 y learned to expect the unexpected.\nBased in Rotterdam and with roots in 
 the Dominican Republic and Indonesia\, she breathes music\, both as a DJ a
 nd on the dance floor. OG Karin mixes everything from different genres and
  finds the common thread in rhythmic\, percussive tracks with raw sounds\,
  always with a healthy dose of groove and sensuality.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-4203e473603dc20b@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T220000Z
DTEND:20260613T000000Z
SUMMARY:Surusinghe
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Fractured beats charged with bass-driven bliss.\n\nSurusinghe i
 s a genre-bending producer known for her innovative and percussive\, bass-
 driven music.\nFrom DJing\, to producing\, promoting\, labels\, and manage
 ment - there isn’t much that Australian born\, London based artist isn't
  involved in. Experimenting with bass\, reggaeton\, broken-beat and techno
 \, Surusinghe keeps her mixes fast and unpredictable.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-86d51c025334242e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T000000Z
DTEND:20260613T020000Z
SUMMARY:Slimfit
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Boisterous & nonconformist Caribbean flavours\n\nSlimfit grew u
 p in an environment where Afro-Caribbean music shared a cabinet with The C
 ure.\nThis may or may not explain the Amsterdam-based artist’s cavalier 
 instincts behind the booth\; a dogma-shattering mix of Latin percussion\, 
 Afro-electronic rhythms\, and explosive rave styles\, where impulsiveness 
 and camp are fully embraced. Slimfit experiments across many disciplines: 
 both behind the decks and beyond\, their work revolves around intuition\, 
 resistance\, and connection.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e27329e5cc12e5c0@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T140000Z
DTEND:20260612T170000Z
SUMMARY:Ketama Man
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Certified dealer in dub\, reggae & dancehall\n\nFor over two de
 cades\, Ketama Man has explored Jamaican music from all possible angles\nI
 t didn’t start with (traditional) DJing\, however\, but as an MC in the 
 late 90s. The physicality of those stage shows gave the necessary insight 
 to translate the best reggae\, dub and dancehall to the clubs. That notion
  of physicality also translates to Ketama Man’s insistence to stick to v
 inyl. That's true dedication in both the selecting and igniting the dance 
 floor part of the sum.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-14a5f005d42c72fe@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T170000Z
DTEND:20260612T190000Z
SUMMARY:Rozaly (Archives)
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:A journey through the musical lineages of Curaçao\n\nRozaly is
  a sonic practitioner\, researcher\, curator\, and DJ from Curaçao.\nHe e
 nshrines all the undiscovered micro-styles from her home region\; a musica
 l ode to friends\, and forgotten pillars of Curaçao musical legacy. Expec
 t lots of echo and reverb\, an odyssey of calypso loops\, 80s Bajan crop-o
 vers\, kompa\, chutney\, and much\, much more.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9f8b57afc3afaa3c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T190000Z
DTEND:20260612T220000Z
SUMMARY:Aba Shanti-I
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:A peerless reggae/dub apostle of the deepest basses\n\nIf roots
  reggae & dub are still resurgent in Europe and the UK\, you better believ
 e Aba Shanti-I is a big reason why.\nSoundsystem culture hauls the party v
 ibes to any place you can set your mind to and over the past three decades
 \, Aba has forged his own unique frequency in this very lineage: distinct 
 manipulations of reverb and delay into existing reggae classics\, translat
 ing into a peerless sound that’s uniquely his.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-1aac1fbc6e345598@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T220000Z
DTEND:20260613T000000Z
SUMMARY:Bony Fly
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Adventurous Caribbean and Latinx productions\n\nProducer\, labe
 l owner and DJ\, Bony Fly has been dubbed as Geneva’s king of dancehall 
 and reggaeton.\nBony Fly’s daredevil production style is the big catalys
 t for getting such distinguished titles\; he combines cutting edge digital
  productions with the more classical\, time-honoured craft of analog mixin
 g\, carving out new possibilities within established dance lineages.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-61104c84a32c15ba@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T000000Z
DTEND:20260613T020000Z
SUMMARY:Mia Koden
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Top shelf bass-heavy rhythms\n\nThe lower frequencies are where
  producer/DJ Mia Koden is most at home\, from the womb to the booth.\nKode
 n\, born Sancha Ndeko\, has keen expertise on how low a bass can indeed go
 \, connecting the dots between dub\, dubstep\, grime and other bass-heavy 
 dance transmutations. Ndeko’s sets bring the rapturous energy of soundsy
 stem block parties to each room or stage: odysseys that span generations\,
  bolster communities and honour undersung histories.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-1e46d36d63b98f72@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T121500Z
DTEND:20260613T130000Z
SUMMARY:Jungle By Night
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Genre-crossing Afrofunk phenomenon\n\nSynergy isn't just the na
 me of a recent collaborative project Jungle By Night sunk their teeth in 
 – it is truly who they are.Jungle By Night has explored virtually every 
 musical style imaginable with thorough\, thoughtful cross-pollination. Dub
 \, krautrock\, psychedelic rock\, pop\, dance\, afrobeat\, hip-hop\, funk\
 , and electronic music all feature in the groundbreaking vocabulary of thi
 s vital collective. Few can bring all those rich influences together and m
 ake people move in ways they never deemed possible.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-6e2e8977a3afb240@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T134500Z
DTEND:20260613T144500Z
SUMMARY:Sylvie Kreusch
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Belgium's cinematic pop superstar\n\nSylvie Kreusch has made wa
 ves as one of Europe's most electrifying stage performers.\nKnown for her 
 expressive lyricism\, strikingly cinematic imagery and genre-fluid sensibi
 lities\, the Belgian artist turned into a celluloid heroine on her latest 
 LP 'Comic Trip'. Her shows leave a carousel of vivid impressions\, from th
 e bigger fireworks to moments of unblemished\, affecting romance.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f6eea264d6bcbcdd@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T154500Z
DTEND:20260613T164500Z
SUMMARY:Ethel Cain
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:The queen of Southern gothic folk pop\n\nEthel Cain is one of p
 op music's most thrilling storytellers\, in both the mainstream and the fr
 inges.\nIn many ways\, Cain covers its familiar themes: the falling in lov
 e\, the coming of age\, the search for identity and belonging. But toss a 
 healthy portion of religious zealotry\, cannibalism and perversion into th
 e cauldron\, and you get of the most shocking and exhilarating musical arc
 s in recent memory. It all plays out like a Southern gothic novel set in 2
 1st Century America.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-693b5070b3593efb@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T174500Z
DTEND:20260613T184500Z
SUMMARY:Mac DeMarco
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Canadian slacker pop savant\n\nMac DeMarco continues to march t
 o his own easygoing beat.\nIn the vast outstretched lands of British Colum
 bia\, Mac is a man who enjoys his canoeing\, his riding of motorcycles and
  his building of water wells. And by the way\, he pens a lot of great jams
  as well. Hence his latest work\, coincidently called ‘Guitar’\, is as
  pure of heart as its creator. Though it seems like Mac is forever winging
  it\, his unmistakable wisdom and wry humor always simmer through.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-44d83368b12bb774@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T200000Z
DTEND:20260613T213000Z
SUMMARY:Gorillaz
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:The most famous animated band on earth\n\nGorillaz is a world i
 n and of itself: vibrant\, urgent and endlessly innovative.\nAlmost three 
 decades in\, the adventures of 2D\, Murdoc Niccals\, Russel Hobbs and Nood
 le have guided us across Plastic Beaches and Cracker Islands\, and now in 
 its ninth episode\, clambering up The Mountain. Indeed\, the novelty of st
 arting an animated band became so much more for founders Damon Albarn and 
 Jamie Hewlett. Behind the celluloid\, Gorillaz has become a cross-generati
 onal\, genre-blending community of legends and current greats – as glori
 ous and vital as ever.\nDive into the world of Gorillaz and read our artic
 le.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ca489e0904a7cc78@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T100000Z
DTEND:20260613T104500Z
SUMMARY:∑tella
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Captivating Mediterranean dream pop\n\nIn Greek songwriter Σte
 lla’s music\, you can literally smell the sea air and the dizzy spells o
 f unspoken attraction.\nHer sultry\, crisply arranged tunes inspire you to
  take a breather from life’s familiar strains\, through the prism of the
  quirky\, vibrant synth-pop of debut LP ‘The Break’ or the more cinema
 tic seaside scenes of ‘Up And Away’. With the latter\, Σtella achieve
 d the milestone of being the first Greek artist to be signed by legendary 
 indie label Sub Pop.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-32d08178d2f58384@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T111500Z
DTEND:20260613T121500Z
SUMMARY:WIES
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Expressive & eclectic Dutch alt-pop\n\nWith an uncanny talent f
 or turning any subject into song\, WIES became one of the most beloved mod
 ern bands in Dutch pop.\nThe group's steady growth hasn’t come at the co
 st of expressing the nuances and finer observations in the obstacle course
  that’s life. The passage of time\, the growing pains\, the hopes and fe
 ars - indeed\, no corners are cut once the curtains open for WIES at Best 
 Kept Secret. And we’re happy to see them return.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5b7bcbc728f6fb47@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T130000Z
DTEND:20260613T134500Z
SUMMARY:Sophie Straat
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Dutch protest singer extraordinaire\n\nSophie Straat feels just
  as much at home on prime time TV as at some grubby grassroots venue\, whi
 ch is very telling about how broadly her work resonates.\nThe Amsterdam-ba
 sed protest singer is a savvy satirist who possesses immense talent for ad
 dressing the ills of the world with maximum entertainment. Stylistically\,
  she veers from Dutch smartlap folk to punk rock on a whim – often with 
 message attached. All-embracing and eternally on the frontlines against in
 justice\, Sophie Straat is one of the most unique and outspoken voices in 
 Dutch pop.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e30db2166f8c72c1@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T144500Z
DTEND:20260613T154500Z
SUMMARY:Don West
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Aussie soul hunk with vintage sound\n\nIn the immortal words of
  Arthur Conley: ‘Do you like good music/ That sweet soul music?’ Austr
 alian singer Don West certainly does.\nSo much so even that West has adopt
 ed his own “coastal” version of that vintage soul lineage: the kind th
 at makes you want to chill beachside with a good book\, or ride a wave or 
 two when the wind’s just right. Obviously\, somewhere in the bedroom wou
 ld also suffice. If West’s honeysweet croon doesn’t take you out immed
 iately\, his striking charisma certainly will.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9a851979072ecb0e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T164500Z
DTEND:20260613T174500Z
SUMMARY:Yard Act
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Dry-witted post-punk dissidents\n\nFrom boy bands\, cowbell dis
 co to MacBeth\, nothing is excluded in the wonderfully witty pocket world 
 of Yard Act.Initially breaking in the post-punk revival's slipstream\, Yar
 d Act quickly separated themselves from the pack of soapbox-shouters with 
 their charmingly flawed character sketches\, offbeat everyman humor and st
 arry-eyed pop sensibility. On their latest LP Where's My Utopia? Yard Act 
 remain as sincere as they are endlessly entertaining.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-8e4493b69e1b5579@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T184500Z
DTEND:20260613T194500Z
SUMMARY:Joey Valence & Brae
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Energetic retro-rap jams\n\nViral sensation and rap duo Joey Va
 lence & Brae are the answer to the question: what if the Beastie Boys had 
 been Gen Zers?\nJoey Valence & Brae's tracks are jam packed with nerdy ref
 erences to pop culture\, memes\, and games. They perform that sweet sample
 -based old-skool rap style with the almost endless possibilities of today.
  For example\, the two childhood friends shot the video for Punk Tactics e
 ntirely on a Nintendo DS. Such fun stunts have earned Joey Valence & Brae 
 a legion of millions of fans.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f25db4ed12255bc3@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T213000Z
DTEND:20260613T223000Z
SUMMARY:Sammy Virji
LOCATION:TWO
DESCRIPTION:Spry UK Garage-reigniter\n\nSammy Virji has quickly made his ma
 rk on the scene and established himself as a pioneer of the UKG renaissanc
 e.\nOver the past eight years\, he's expanded his discography and created 
 an unforgettable live show. After his iconic single "Shella Verse" featuri
 ng Flowdan and his viral DJ Mag stream\, he's become an indispensable part
  of the dance world. With his new album\, "If U Need It\," he's steadily g
 rowing his fan base. Sammy is bringing UKG to a wider audience while simul
 taneously developing and refining his own sound.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9040766e8ddad86a@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T104500Z
DTEND:20260613T113000Z
SUMMARY:Dressed Like Boys
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Intimate & resonant pop phenomenon\n\nDressed Like Boys\, the s
 olo project of artist Jelle Denturck\, is both intrusively intimate and st
 unningly grandiose.The Ghent-based songwriter tackles his experiences as a
  gay man from personal history\, as well as the history of humankind\, wit
 hin a framework of timeless pop staples like The Beatles\, David Bowie\, S
 ufjan Stevens and Elton John. Though Denturck’s songs are often rooted i
 n hardship and struggle\, they always breach the soil with uncanny emotion
 al power and spirited flair – his self-titled debut staking its place as
  a modern classic of Belgian pop.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-279dbcbd1ea2c4ee@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T121500Z
DTEND:20260613T130000Z
SUMMARY:Mên An Tol
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Fresh-faced folk-inspired guitar anthems\n\nMên An Tol are nam
 ed after an ancient rock formation in their native Cornish\, which may tel
 l you something about their overall approach to rock music.\nIn this high 
 velocity society\, you see an increasing number of bands harken back to th
 e communal\, nostalgic spirit of folk. Mên An Tol are fresh faces in this
  scene\, already obtaining big fans in Fontaines DC and The Libertines wit
 h their bittersweet & timeless anthems – the kind of music that’ll tan
 talise fans of The Waterboys\, The Pogues and R.E.M..
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-27257f8d0f947adb@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T134500Z
DTEND:20260613T143000Z
SUMMARY:Skullcrusher
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Spectral folk of quiet devastation\n\nQuietude can be extremely
  heavy\, something Skullcrusher’s hazy alt-folk most certainly illustrat
 es.\nFunny thing: the Skullcrusher moniker was hatched by Helen Ballentine
  when she started a DJ project mixing My Bloody Valentine and Autechre. Wh
 en that didn't pan out\, it just stuck when she decided to pen haunting fi
 nger-picking folk songs that seem to exist inside of a David Lynch or Kiyo
 shi Kurasawa picture. Skullcrusher expertly treads a fine line between bea
 uty and devastation.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ebfb43a2b0d61e8a@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T153000Z
DTEND:20260613T163000Z
SUMMARY:Getdown Services
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Jolly have-a-go 'power disco' hijinks\n\nThe ‘plan’ behind 
 Getdown Services was to have no plan at all: except basking in some fearle
 ss fumbling about and fun.\nThis sense of abandon morphs into a thrifty mi
 x of eighties pop\, post-punk\, and classic rock that’s frequently been 
 dubbed as ‘power disco’. Indeed\, these two freewheeling Bristolians s
 eem to make it up as they go along\, and it often unfolds in similar comed
 ic brilliance as in that famous sitcom “Peep Show”. A love for all thi
 ngs music-related\, from Chic to AC/DC\, is worn on Getdown Services' furr
 owed sleeves.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-878117e0528ceb83@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T173000Z
DTEND:20260613T183000Z
SUMMARY:Genesis Owusu
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Bombshell blender of rap\, post-punk & indie\n\nOne of his LPs 
 might be called Struggler\, the way Ghanaian/Australian artist Genesis Owu
 su mixes styles like post-punk\, rap\, pop\, funk and electro feels downri
 ght effortless.\nA Bloc Party riff here\, a lo-fi beat there\, a string se
 ction out of nowhere – Owusu's songs forge unity by means of the most in
 explicable of spare parts. His singular creativity as a producer is matche
 d by his subversive sharp-witted wordplay. Lawless\, formless\, thoughtles
 s\, flawless!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-75f9b9fcbc324cee@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T193000Z
DTEND:20260613T203000Z
SUMMARY:Gelli Haha
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Wacky\, wonky cartoon pop\n\nGelli Haha pens magnetic and kalei
 doscopic synth pop/electroclash tunes that seem to tumble straight out of 
 a Dr. Seuss-novel.\nThe music of the Los Angeles-based artist is merely th
 e starting point: the self-coined Gelliverse paints all surroundings into 
 a multi-coloured big top spectacle one can not help but be immersed in. Th
 e perfect live experience for unleashing your inner infant.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9f029c84c82e4370@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T214500Z
DTEND:20260613T223000Z
SUMMARY:Parker Fans
LOCATION:The Secret
DESCRIPTION:Mischief-making indie boogie trio\n\nThere’s a fuzzy sentimen
 t to Parker Fans’ self-described ‘three-way boogie bromance’\, shuff
 ling styles with a magpie’s spirit.Gabber house flirtations\, hip-hop ho
 edowns\, breakbeat bonanzas: this Dutch trio has a knack for courting all 
 kinds of unexpected chaos – often of the gleeful variety. Fully aware of
  the futility of having too much fun\, Parker Fans are squiggly\, scatterb
 rained and compulsively scene-causing.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-578e9139c8ef8ec7@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T100000Z
DTEND:20260613T120000Z
SUMMARY:DJ St. Paul
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:The Floor manager who lets it all happen\n\nDJ St. Paul aka the
  pundit behind Pop-O-Matic\, aka the honcho of Let It Happen\, aka the chi
 ef facilitator of Best Kept Secret's The Floor.Paul isn’t a floor manage
 r like those at normal work environments\; it’s all play in his book. Ev
 ery year he invites an uncanny list of guests from all corners and crevice
 s of the music world – blasting the biggest hits\, the most vital niches
  & subcultures\, the juiciest of deep cuts\, and everything inbetween at T
 he Floor. It’s quite literally all hands on deck when St. Paul’s your 
 host – an exploration of pure dance-floor euphoria in all its vast devia
 tions. An individual eternally ready for both the moment and the sound.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-4f975d313f3df1cb@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T120000Z
DTEND:20260613T124500Z
SUMMARY:Sheyma (Live)
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:A commanding voice blending Western and Arab culture\n\nBreatht
 aking singer with a live performance that blends electronic beats and trad
 itional Arab music.\nOne of the crowd favourites at the recent edition of 
 the Grauzone Festival\, Sheyma Rochdi is destroying boring borders with he
 r sound\, one as intimate as it is riotous. A voice that needs to be heard
  to be believed. Sheyma's music is inspired by influences from different g
 enres of Moroccan music such as Gnawa music\, Moroccan Chaabi mixed with A
 rabic alternative. While her vocals are connected to traditions of Arabic 
 music\, the structures of the songs are very remote from its codes. True f
 reedom this way lies.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-6a51f82fa58a1492@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T124500Z
DTEND:20260613T131500Z
