BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-9caedc231dd689dc@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T100000Z
DTEND:20260613T104500Z
SUMMARY:Apichat Pakwan
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Balmy blend of Thai music & electronics\n\nApichat Pakwan bring
 s a lively crossover of electronics and Thai esan and molam movements: the
  sweetest balance between the modern and the traditional.It unfolds miracu
 lously live as well: you have producer Olivier Schreuder serving up beats 
 that blend seamlessly with the Thai musicians and singers: not in that cru
 de mash-up kind of way\, but warmly courting each other in a tryst. This a
 pproach carries over to audiences\, creating a hot & sweltering dancefloor
  environment.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-4ea6bb55575d00cd@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T111500Z
DTEND:20260613T120000Z
SUMMARY:DYGL
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Japanese garage rock torch bearers\n\nJapanese garage rockers D
 YGL (pronounced 'day glo') embody pure exuberance and rebellion with their
  catchy-as-sin anthems.\nThat the four piece's swagger and songwriting acu
 men holds up against any of their forebears in evident in the fact that Th
 e Strokes' Albert Hammond Jr. decided to take it upon himself to produce D
 YGL's debut album. So who's in the house?Curated by Tramhaus
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-6087f17bc509031e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T123000Z
DTEND:20260613T131500Z
SUMMARY:Servo
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Brutal psych noise beast\n\nFrench trio Servo are a high mass o
 f pure uncompromising noise rock: dangerous\, devastating and no wasted mo
 vements.\nBrandishing locomotive rhythms\, noise hexes of the spine-chilli
 ng variety and demonic vocals\, Servo aren’t concerned with adding tons 
 of bells and whistles: their songs go straight for the jugular and send au
 diences right back to the stone ages. Hunting season is open this summer. 
 Curated by Tramhaus
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-92ed51cb5fb6b09c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T134500Z
DTEND:20260613T143000Z
SUMMARY:Good Flying Birds
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Lo-fi jangle pop up-and-comers\n\nGood Flying Birds are a young
  band who are happy being a throwback: capturing contagious powerpop gems 
 with lo-fi home recordings.\nIt’s no coincidence they are named after a 
 Guided By Voices-song\, a band emblematic of such a sprightly modus operan
 di. Delightfully chaotic\, hodgepodge and impulsive\, the chaos Good Flyin
 g Birds sow with a bunch of instruments in the room seems to inevitably ma
 nifest into tunes you’ll hum along for days on end.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d28c6ff305eafabb@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T151500Z
DTEND:20260613T160000Z
SUMMARY:Another Country $$$$
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Genre-fluid experimental rock enigma\n\nManchester experimental
  outfit Another Country $$$$ has no qualms jumping into the deep end: whol
 ly unconcerned with genre tropes\, eternally fluid and free.\nExperimental
  rock\, IDM\, ambient pop\, mathcore: defining Another Country $$$$ is dep
 endent on who you ask. The group’s creativity isn’t based on fixed out
 comes\, but constant metamorphosis. Chalk it up to a constant remix\, comp
 ulsively courting uncharted sonic expressways.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-20f71d8bf5e73ba7@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T164500Z
DTEND:20260613T173000Z
SUMMARY:C'est Qui?
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Politically-charged\, powder keg punk anthems\n\nC’est Qui? w
 on’t settle for compromise within their witty\, politically-charged punk
  tunes.Anger is just the tip of the iceberg for this plucky young outfit: 
 sadness\, frustration\, despair\, resilience and joy\; these are the very 
 roots from which their scuzzy\, outspoken anthems sprout. C’est Qui? suc
 k out the poison from society’s festering wounds with pure exuberance an
 d explosiveness.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-110ef7392aa6d7bc@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T181500Z
DTEND:20260613T190000Z
SUMMARY:Lime Garden
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:Hook-heavy & heartfelt indie pop\n\nLime Garden’s irresistibl
 e blend of post-punk\, synth pop\, and indie rock marries romance with the
  mundane.On sophomore album Maybe Not Tonight\, the Brighton band illustra
 te the fickle dynamics of nightlife – where starry-eyed expectations and
  frantic fun can promptly spiral into melancholy and chaos. Beneath an end
 less array of cheeky hooks\, sizzling melodies and plunging rhythms\, Lime
  Garden’s brilliance rests on a fundamental force: their friendship.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ac03b36d6cc309e6@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T200000Z
DTEND:20260613T220000Z
SUMMARY:WK Nederland - Japan
LOCATION:The Casbah
DESCRIPTION:The World Cup match Netherlands – Japan will be broadcast at 
 The Casbah\, presented by Kartje Kilo!
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-7c18b03bdde1d15e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T110000Z
DTEND:20260613T114500Z
SUMMARY:de Volkskrant: Ondertussen in de Kosmos
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:Tijdreizen: het kan tóch!\n\nDe populaire wetenschapspodcast v
 an de Volkskrant\, Ondertussen in de Kosmos\, beantwoordt bij deze livesho
 w fascinerende vragen over de tijd.\nZoals: waarom lijkt de tijd gevoelsma
 tig soms zo snel te gaan\, en soms juist zo langzaam? Tikt de tijd overal 
 in het heelal even snel? En: is tijdreizen mogelijk? (Spoiler alert: 'JA!'
 )\nPlease note: This program item is in Dutch.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d8c6cc7b680081ac@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T120000Z
DTEND:20260613T124500Z
SUMMARY:Universiteit van Nederland - De slaapwetenschapper
LOCATION:Not Nothing
DESCRIPTION:De slaapwetenschapper houd je wakker\n\nHeb je die acht uur sla
 ap wel echt nodig? Hoe zorg je dat je lekker in slaap valt? En wat zeggen 
 mijn dromen over mij? Merijn vd Laar neemt je in een interactieve talk mee
  door de slaap en droomwereld. Vragen stellen mag! Met Merijn van de Laar\
 , slaapwetenschapper Maastricht University\nPlease note: This program item
  is in Dutch
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
